description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you looking to gain experience in Medical Education or Quality Improvement or Simulation or Paediatric Emergency Medicine or an area of your choice? &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have &lt;strong&gt;3&lt;/strong&gt; exciting NEW Portfolio Paediatric Middle Grade posts developed in line with the Health Board’s Clinical Futures Strategy. Based at our new flag ship Grange University Hospital, Cwmbran upon its opening in November 2020. Paediatric facilities include an integrated Children’s Emergency Assessment comprising 16 assessment spaces, adjacent 6 bed Short Stay Unit, 2 bedded Stabilisation &amp; High Dependency Unit, and 48 bed inpatient ward. The Multidisciplinary Education Centre is equipped with the latest AV technology and there is a purpose built simulation suite and clinical skills lab.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Post holders will have a full 1:10 out of hours commitment but 40% of paid in-hours’ time will be dedicated to improving your portfolio.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have created specific opportunities but would be open to other suggestions:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Teaching&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Simulation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Quality Improvement (General)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Quality Improvement (Healthier Together) &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Paediatric Emergency Medicine &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Paediatric Diabetes&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Paediatric Neurodisability:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an ideal opportunity to gain experience and improve your CV to reapply to ST Training in future, acquire new skills as OOPE or improve your CV for CESR.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Aneurin Bevan University Health Board is responsible for the healthcare of more than 600,000 residents in South East Wales, providing acute and primary services, plus a wide range of community and mental health care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Staff wellbeing is a Health Board priority, with a comprehensive package of support and development opportunities available to all.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These positions involves Regulated Activity with children as defined by the Safeguarding Vulnerable Groups Act (amended by the Protection of Freedoms Act 2012) and the following checks will be undertaken following any conditional offer:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Enhanced check with barred list information, including a children’s barred list check&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants must hold or be eligible to hold full registration and a licence to practice with the GMC.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THIS IS A NON TRAINING POST &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Those wishing to discuss the posts informally in the first instance or arrange a visit to the Department should contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Yvette Cloete, Consultant Paediatrician &amp; Clinical Futures Lead Tel: 01873 732479&lt;/p&gt;
